While some people think governments should only spend money on public services without cosiderations for arts, I disagree.
This essay will demonstrate this through personal benefits and social benefits.

The primary reason is that the arts improve people's quality of life. This is because people can enjoy music, movies and all kinds of stuff, which help them relax. Consequently, people can have a happier and healthier life. For instance, many families visit museums or watch movies together in weekends. This shows that the arts bring enjoyment and relaxation to people's daily lives.

Another important consideration is that the arts create jobs. If the government supports the arts, more people would have job opportunities. In other words, the arts help the economy as well as culture. A case in point is artists, actors and museum workers, who can earn a living because of arts. Therefore, spending money on the arts also benefits society.

Admittedly, opponents may contend that government money is limited, so it should be spent only on public services. There is still some truth in this. However, this overlooks the fact that both public services and the arts are important for different groups of people, so both need government support.

In conclusion, although government money is limited, I maintain that governments should also spend money on the arts, by they improve people's lives and benefit society.